git commands 

git init for creating local repository

git config --global user.name sai

git config --global user.email narendrasai316@gmail.com

git config --list

git add filename to stage environment

git commit -m "message for upload to local repository"

git remote add origin url 

git push origin master

to create bare repository git init --bare

ssh root@ip to login in to remote system(destination) from devolopers system(source)

to authenticate we have to modify file sshd_config in /etc/ssh/sshd_config

edit these 3 
	permitroot login          enable
	pubkey authentication      enable
	password authentication    yes

systemctl stop sshd
systemctl status sshd
systemctl stop sshd

sudo passwd root

create new password

sudo bash

password N@rendr@s@i888

to connect password less authentication generate keys

ssh-keygen

they are stored in .ssh folder in c /user/naren

ssh-copy-id root@ip

git remote add origin root@1ip:/root/git

if any mistakes in giving the path go to reset above link : git remote set-url origin root@ip:path of repository

git blame filename

git mergetool

git log

git log --oneline

git branch                                          to know how many branches in that workspace

git branch <branch name>                            to create new branch

git checkout <branch name>                          to change from one branch to other

git checkout -b <branch name>                       to create new branch and to change to that branch

git branch -v                                       to know latest commits in every branch in that workspace

git branch -a                                       to list the local and remote branches

git branch -r                                       to list remote branches

git branch -d <branch name>                         to delete the branch in local repo. it shows warning when we dont merge properly before deleting 

git branch -D <branch name>                         to delete the branch in local repo without any warning

git push <remote repo> :refs/heads/branch name      to delete branch in remote repo

git tag 